      "review_summary": "The PR removes `argsMenu: \"auto\"` from the built-in `/usage` command registration while leaving `nativeName: \"usage\"` and the shared usage handler in place.\n\nPR surface: Source -1. Total -1 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: `/usage full` parses a `mode` value and makes `resolveCommandArgMenu` return `null`, while current followup delivery still does not append `responseUsage` footers. I did not run a live Docker plus Telegram reproduction in this read-only review.",
